<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFA6BA0AB46FF0B9B60BF787" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" type="activity">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFA6BA0AB46FF0B9B60BF787" blockId="26.[125,1333,1101,2359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFFA6BA0AB46FF0B9B34AF834" bold="true" box="[125,364,2009,2042]" pageId="26" pageNumber="645">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Duke of Abruzzi’s Free-tailed Bats are nocturnal. Most individuals were netted over water or in clearings, but one individual was obtained from a day roost in a crevice in the trunk of an 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA6BA0AB66BFF4CB164F787" box="[633,834,2092,2121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Isoberlinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="doka">Isoberlinia doka</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA6BA0AB744FF4CB1FCF787" box="[854,986,2092,2121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) tree.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFA6BA0AB46DFF30B338F729" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFA6BA0AB46DFF30B338F729" blockId="26.[125,1333,1101,2359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFFA6BA0AB46DFF30B163F7BF" bold="true" box="[127,837,2128,2161]" pageId="26" pageNumber="645">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Duke of Abruzzi’s Free-tailed Bats are found in small groups. The individual obtained from a day roost in an 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA6BA0AB0A3FF17B713F756" box="[1201,1333,2167,2200]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Isoberlinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Isoberlinia</taxonomicName>
doka tree was found along with a large roost of ¢.150 Angolan Free-tailed Bats (
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA6BA0AB0FFFFFFB32DF729" authorityName="A. Smith" authorityYear="1833" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Mops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="condylurus">Mops condylurus</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFA6BA0AB46DFF92B6BCF6C1" box="[127,1178,2290,2319]" pageId="26" pageNumber="645" type="conservation">
